100. Semivirumque.] In rivalry of Ovid's famous line, Ars Am, 11. 24, on Minotaur.

103. Tum caput irrorans] Mock baptism into a Trinity os Powers, viz.. Acheron, Per- sephone, and Dis (i.c.‚ Pluto). Aeolides (1‘.c.‚ Sisyphus) is a nickname as frequently given to him (agn, l. 260) as Onopordus. See Johnston’s allusion to this youthful satire in XXXVIII.

117. Hominum . . . artus.] Mandrake. See IV. l. 256 and note.
